=== Parliamentary QA ===
Title: Trend of Vaping
Date: 11 May 2021
Document Type: Parliamentary QA (Written Answer)
Topic: Vaping trends, enforcement, youth awareness, online sales

Summary:
- Question: Monitoring vaping trends, mitigating online sales, and raising awareness among teens.
- Ministry of Health (MOH) and Health Sciences Authority (HSA) response:
  1. Trend Monitoring:
     - Observed an increase in seized e-vaporisers in 2019, continuing into 2020.
     - Number of cases involving sale or possession of e-vaporisers increased over the same period.
  2. Enforcement Against Sale and Import:
     - HSA works with Immigration & Checkpoints Authority (ICA) to interdict smuggled e-vaporisers, including via parcels and online orders.
     - Active online surveillance and enforcement against online sales.
     - Collaboration with online platforms (Instagram, Carousell, Facebook, e-commerce sites) to remove illegal sale postings; over 2,000 postings removed in 2020.
  3. Public Awareness and Education:
     - HPB works with Ministry of Education and Institutes of Higher Learning to educate youths on tobacco-free lifestyle benefits and to remain vape-free.
     - Uses online learning activities and gamification (e.g., virtual escape rooms), self-directed resources, and educator training.
     - Information also available on HealthHub.
  4. Legal Reminders:
     - Importation, sale, distribution, purchase, use, and possession of e-vaporisers and accessories prohibited under Tobacco (Control of Advertisements and Sale) Act (TCASA).
     - MOH continues to work with partner agencies for access control and public education.

Key Entities:
- Ministry of Health (MOH)  
- Health Sciences Authority (HSA)  
- Immigration & Checkpoints Authority (ICA)  
- Health Promotion Board (HPB)  
- Ministry of Education (MOE)  
- Institutes of Higher Learning (IHLs)  

Key Concepts:
- Monitoring of vaping trends and seizures  
- Enforcement against online and physical sales  
- Youth education via gamification and resources  
- Legal prohibition under TCASA

Author / Issuer:
Ministry of Health (MOH), Health Sciences Authority (HSA), Health Promotion Board (HPB)
Date of Issue: 11 May 2021
